Extracts the coefficients and confidence intervals from a ds.glm or ds.glmSLMA model.

Source: R/lm-tab.R
dh.lmTab.Rd

Extracts the coefficients and confidence intervals from a ds.glm or ds.glmSLMA model.

dh.lmTab(
  model = NULL,
  type = NULL,
  coh_names = NULL,
  direction = c("long", "wide"),
  ci_format = NULL,
  family = "gaussian",
  round_digits = 2,
  exp = FALSE
)

Arguments

model

saved output from either ds.glm, ds.glmSLMA or ds.lmerSLMA
type

either "ipd", "slma" or "lmer"
coh_names

a vector of cohort names. Note this needs to be in the same order as the cohorts provided to the model.
direction

either "long" or "wide"
ci_format

format for the confidence intervals when direction == "wide". "separate" outputs separate columns with upper and lower CIs. "paste" adds these in brackets to the coefficient.'
family

where type is ipd or slma, specify the family used in the model
round_digits

Number of decimal places to use in table. Default is 2.
exp

specify whether you want odds ratios to be exponentiated

Value

A tibble containing the estimate with lower and upper confidence intervals
